id de se ipso loquitur: Galen, de Plac. Hipp. et Plat. lv 7 p. 418, says that Posidonius, in criticising Chrysippus’ de— finition of aegritudo, employs the story of what Anaxagoras said on hearing of the death of his son and said that it was
